          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Natural tantalum targets of 2.54 cm diameter and 0.12",
                "mm thickness with mass of 1.2 g containing only 140",
                "microg of 180mTa."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " De-excitation cross section of the isomeric-",
                "state nuclide 180mTa has been measured with",
                "mono-energetic photon beams in the 1.56 MeV to 3.70",
                "MeV energy range. After irradiation for typically 20",
                "h with photon fluxes ranging from 0.3*10**7",
                "gamma/(cm2*s) to 3.2*10**7 gamma/(cm2*s), the 180mTa",
                "de-excitation cross section was obtained from the",
                "yield of the Kalpha1 and Kalpha2 X rays of 180mHf at",
                "55.79 keV and 54.61 keV, respectively, produced after",
                "electron capture on the unstable 180mTa ground state.",
                "The tantalum disks were gamma-ray counted with a",
                "planar HPGe detector. For this purpose the disk was",
                "attached directly to the front face of the 30 mm",
                "diameter detector. Its efficiency was measured in the",
                "region of interest with a calibrated multi-isotope",
                "gamma-ray source, including 241Am with X rays at",
                "59.54 keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The uncertainty assigned to the data include",
                "the statistical uncertainties plus an estimated 25%",
                "uncertainty in bremsstrahlung correction, except at",
                "Egamma=1.8 MeV, where a 18% uncertainty was used.",
                "The latter two uncertainties are estimates based on",
                "the present single-electron and two-electron bunch",
                "tests and past experience. All individual",
                "uncertainties were added in quadrature."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-1",
                "minimum_value": 18.0,
                "maximum_value": 25.0,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Bremsstrahlung correction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A sizable attenuation correction of 1.3 had to be",
                "applied, using the X-ray attenuation factor. A small",
                "correction was applied to account for the slightly",
                "different electron beam currents used at some of the",
                "energies. The bremsstrahlung correction."
              ]
            }
          ],
